Regression task

dfii <- df %>% 
  mutate(y = boot::logit( (response - 0) / (100 - 0) ) ) %>% 
  select(R, G, B, 
         Lightness, Saturation, Hue,
         y)

                         refresh = 0)

plot(mod01, pars = names(mod01$coefficients)) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "grey", linetype = "dashed", size = 1.) +
  theme_bw()

purrr::map2_dfr(list(mod01),
                as.character(1),
                function(mod, mod_name){as.data.frame(mod) %>% tibble::as_tibble() %>% 
                    select(sigma) %>% 
                    mutate(model_name = mod_name)}) %>% 
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = sigma)) +
  geom_freqpoly(bins = 55,
                 mapping = aes(color = model_name),
                 size = 1.1) +
  ggthemes::scale_color_colorblind("Model") +
  theme_bw()

The posterior is precise. The sigma is known and is almost normally distributed with a peak at 0.082.

Posterior visualization

plot(mod02, pars = names(mod02$coefficients)) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "grey", linetype = "dashed", size = 1.) +
  theme_bw()

purrr::map2_dfr(list(mod02),
                as.character(1),
                function(mod, mod_name){as.data.frame(mod) %>% tibble::as_tibble() %>% 
                    select(sigma) %>% 
                    mutate(model_name = mod_name)}) %>% 
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = sigma)) +
  geom_freqpoly(bins = 55,
                 mapping = aes(color = model_name),
                 size = 1.1) +
  ggthemes::scale_color_colorblind("Model") +
  theme_bw()
